The paper deals with a communication system that involves multiple base stations and a single mobile station, which falls under the category of wireless communication networks. The paper proposes a new scheme for spatial modulation, which is a technique used in wireless communication systems to increase spectral efficiency. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also deals with the use of precoding to improve the performance of the system, which falls under the category of communication (cs.COMM). The use of multiple base stations to communicate with a single mobile station is a characteristic of a macro-diversity system, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also deals with the optimization of the system, which involves the use of algorithms and mathematical models, falling under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with the design and implementation of a novel communication system, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
